Cribs for Kids® National Infant Safe Sleep Initiative
Yesterday at 12:55 PM ·

Creating a #safesleep plan for your baby is the best way to assure that they are protected from a sleep-related death or injury.

It really is as easy as remembering your ABC’s!

Always make sure that your baby is Alone, on their Back and in a safety-approved Crib for every sleep, at nap time, and at bedtime.

Your baby’s crib should be free of crib bumpers, blankets, stuffed toys, and pillows and should only have a tightly fitted sheet on a firm mattress.

Your baby should always be placed to sleep on their back and should never sleep anywhere other than their crib. Sleeping with your baby in an adult bed, or on a chair or couch can lead to tragedy.

Learn more about infant safe sleep by visiting our online Safe Sleep Academy - https://www.safesleepacademy.org/

#cribsforkids #SIDS #SUID #babylove #babylife #mom #newmomlife #newmomtips #newdad #expectingmom #expectingparents #expectingababy #expecting #BabySafetyMonth

University of Kentucky Family and Consumer Sciences Extension
September 10 at 12:27 PM ·

Today is World Suicide Prevention Day. It’s a time to remember those affected by suicide, to raise awareness, and to focus efforts on directing treatment to those who need it most.

#BeThe1To is the National Suicide Prevention Lifeline’s message for National Suicide Prevention Month and beyond. It helps spread the word about actions we can all take to prevent suicide. The Lifeline network and its partners are working to change the conversation from suicide to suicide prevention, to actions that can promote healing, help and give hope.

The Lifeline network provides free and confidential 24/7 support for people in distress, prevention and crisis resources for you or your loved ones, and best practices for professionals. To learn more, visit https://suicidepreventionlifeline.org/

Lake Cumberland District Health Department
September 9 at 12:51 PM ·

The LCDHD is excited to partner with the BOUNCE Coalition to provide a FREE virtual training via zoom on "Building on Your Child's Strengths". There are no additional required classes or purchases, it is provided free to our community.

Often, parents/grandparents/caregivers focus on the problems and challenges their children/grandchildren face. This workshop is designed to teach parents/grandparents/caregivers how to identify the strengths their child/grandchild possesses and to help them build on those strengths to grow up successfully. The training uses the age-specific practical methods and encourages parents/grandparents/caregivers to put the learning into action.

Please register by clicking on the flier or call 1-800-928-4416 x 5.
#lcdhd

University of Kentucky Family and Consumer Sciences Extension added a new photo to the album: Healthy at Home Calendar.
September 8 at 10:36 AM ·

For today's #HealthyAtHome prompt, we encourage you to accept the things you cannot change. There is much uncertainty around us, but we have the ability to control how we react and respond in all situations. If there is something particularly unsettling, participate in today's activity challenge and dance it out! This aerobic activity is great exercise for the body, but also for our mood. Turn on your favorite song and dance however you like during the duration. Having fun? Turn on a playlist and dance around the house for a few songs!
---
On Wednesday, our daily prompt focuses on avoiding negativity and unhealthy outlets. Take time to practice self-care to help reduce stressors. A few ideas:
🔹Go for a leisurely walk
🔹Read a book
🔹Spend time on your favorite hobby
🔹Have a homemade spa night: do a face mask, give yourself a manicure or pedicure, take a relaxing bath
🔹Catch up on your favorite TV show or start a new series
🔹Sit outdoors and watch the sunset

On behalf of Summer Servings, I would like to thank our community for the out pouring support given over the summer. We were able to provide grocery assistance for 20 families, and it would not have been possible with out the backing of our community and school system! I would also like to personally applaud our school system for allowing children back into the schools this week. I know so many of them needed not only the meals provided, but the love offered inside of those walls! With that being said, during the NTI weeks ahead, GC school system will be offering a meal delivery program . However, if you know of a student that needs supplements in addition to the meal delivery, please contact us! Proud to call GC home! 💚💛🐲

Green County Schools
June 25 at 10:31 AM ·

Everyone has a story… this is ours!

We take great pride in the quality of services we can provide for the children and youth in our community. At every level of development, from Pre-Schoolers spending their first days in a school building to our graduating seniors that have been prepared for the major life transitions ahead, we provide higher-level learning while also enriching academic achievement with a great variety of co—curricular and extra-curricular opportunities.

The guide linked below provides a listing of opportunities available at each of our five schools including:
- Green County Primary School (Pre-K to 2nd Grade)
- Green County Intermediate School (3rd Grade – 5th Grade)
- Green County Middle School (6th Grade – 8th Grade)
- Green County High School (9th Grade – 12th Grade)
- Green County Area Technology Center (8th Grade – 12th Grade)

https://drive.google.com/file/d/1iOjEVOtWQBv_WhXf7F18UbwEPCFgFwe_/view?usp=sharing

#GCSchools #WeCARE

Music from BenSound.

shared_text:
Michael Lemon‎Cyber Safe Teen Nation (for Parents of Online Teens And Tweens)
June 8 at 6:19 AM ·

After speaking with principals and several other school administrators last week, one thing is clear...no one knows.

When will school start, what happens if the numbers spike, will we be on NTI for the entire year?

The only thing that is clear is that our kids are online more than ever and the predators are online in force.

Our kids need to be educated in the dangers of pedophiles, cyber bullies and consequences of their own poor decisions.

They need to be protected and guided by knowledgeable adults.

We can help with both of those needs with our new online training:
•Safer kids
•Smarter parents and school staff
•Personal Development Hours (available if approved)

Could your school use help educating them and keep them safe, even if they are at home???

Give me a 👍 and I will shoot you a PM to start the conversation.

Mike

shared_text:
University of Kentucky Family and Consumer Sciences Extension added a new photo to the album: Healthy at Home Calendar.
June 4 at 2:47 PM ·

Today's #HealthyAtHome calendar prompt includes lower body exercises, including squats. Squats are an effective move that can improve strength throughout the body, however, proper form is key to do so safely. Keep your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointing forward, and back straight. Keep your eyes forward and chest lifted. Descend as if you are going to sit into a chair, keep your knees in line with your toes, and your heels on the ground. Only descend as far as you feel comfortable before contracting back to standing.

For today’s activity, complete a short workout circuit. Complete 10 squats and hop on 1 leg (20 seconds per leg) for 2-3 reps. This movement snack will give your legs a quick workout!

Keep your eyes forward and chest lifted. Descend as if you are going to sit into a chair, keep your knees in line with your toes, and your heels on the ground. Only descend as far as you feel comfortable before contracting back to standing.

REMINDER concerning information regarding pandemic EBT benefits:
Kentucky families with students who normally receive free or reduced-price meals at school may be eligible to receive financial assistance through the Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) program. The P-EBT program is an emergency nutrition assistance funding program for:

Families already receiving assistance can receive P-EBT.
Children who already receive SNAP, Kentucky Transitional Assistance Program, Kinship Care or Medicaid will receive P-EBT on their EBT cards and do not need to apply separately.

University of Kentucky Family and Consumer Sciences Extension added a new photo to the album: Healthy at Home Calendar.
April 29 at 3:00 PM ·

While technology has enhanced our lives, and is a tremendous asset while staying #HealthyAtHome, it can also be a detriment to our health. Excessive media use is not good for our physical, mental, or emotional well-being for various reasons.

While it can be difficult to unplug completely during this time, we can do our best to reduce our screen time. By doing so, we may find increased mindfulness, improved sleep, deeper connections with those closest to us, and enhanced productivity.

How can you reduce your technology use this week?

post_text:
Good Morning and Happy Monday! Due to COVID-19 the Community Baby Shower scheduled for Thursday, April 16th has been postponed.
Even though the shower will not take place this week, the Green County YSC will be posting some educational information for new and expectant moms each day and will be giving away some much needed baby essentials throughout the week, right here on the YSC page. 🥰
Please share this information with any Green County expectant mom so she can get in on the fun!

If you are expecting, please send me a private message so that I can get you in the drawings for the week. Just leave me your name, phone number and due date. Thanks in advance!! :)

Speaking of essentials....the first assignment is for all those veteran moms that have been through babyhood a few times, please list some "must haves" for our expectant moms. I will choose something from this list to give away!!

alreadyhttps://www.parents.com/baby/care/newborn/10-things-to-know-about-newborns/
shared_text:
PARENTS.COM
10 Things to Know About Newborns
text:
Good Morning and Happy Monday! Due to COVID-19 the Community Baby Shower scheduled for Thursday, April 16th has been postponed.
Even though the shower will not take place this week, the Green County YSC will be posting some educational information for new and expectant moms each day and will be giving away some much needed baby essentials throughout the week, right here on the YSC page. 🥰
Please share this information with any Green County expectant mom so she can get in on the fun!

If you are expecting, please send me a private message so that I can get you in the drawings for the week. Just leave me your name, phone number and due date. Thanks in advance!! :)

Speaking of essentials....the first assignment is for all those veteran moms that have been through babyhood a few times, please list some "must haves" for our expectant moms. I will choose something from this list to give away!!

alreadyhttps://www.parents.com/baby/care/newborn/10-things-to-know-about-newborns/

PARENTS.COM
10 Things to Know About Newborns

March 30 at 5:22 PM ·

Who is ready for Extension To Go bag #2??? This week, the topic is Mindful Eating. Mindful eating is is selecting foods your body needs for good health and learning to enjoy the experience of eating. Along with some great information, the bags will include ingredients to make a healthy snack! (The recipe is kid friendly but is enjoyable for any age.) Bags will be available for pickup beginning Wednesday morning and will be out until they have all been claimed. There will be a limited number available.

shared_text:
Michael Lemon‎Cyber Safe Teen Nation (for Parents of Online Teens And Tweens)
March 20 at 12:27 PM ·

To all our FRYSC partners, teachers, administrators and school staff stepping up to the plate truly living the “Whatever It Takes” life...we see what you are doing and say thank you.

So instead of just saying thank you, we are going to give back to those that are giving so much.

Chris Brown made me these Bourbon Barrel Heads and Barrel Rings for the FRYSC Victory Over Violence conference (Chris said he can make more for you).

During times like this, I figure the least I can do is brighten a few FRYSC’s day.

So, no share the page, tag 5 friends crap.

If you are a FRYSC, just tag your FRYSC or school’s Facebook page in this post.

If you would like to nominate a Family Resource Youth Service Center Coordinator, just tag their center or the school Facebook Page in this post and they are entered.

This way we know who to thank for their service.

We will select 2 winners from the comments on Wednesday.

Thanks for doing what you do.

Mike

Green County Schools
March 18 at 1:24 PM ·

Medical Clinic Info!!

💚❤️💚❤️💚❤️

THE HEALTHY KIDS CLINIC of GREEN COUNTY is offering TELEHEALTH services from the comfort and safety of your own home from 8am-3pm cst Monday-Friday. This service is available to staff, student's and their family members in GREEN COUNTY. TELEHEALTH is a virtual visit with a APRN from HEALTHY KIDS CLINIC to treat minor illnesses without having to leave your home. If any medications are prescribed, they will be sent electronically to your pharmacy.

To schedule a TELEHEALTH visit is as simple as 1-2-3!

Call the Healthy Kids Clinic at 1-844-435-0900 to schedule your appt.
Download the ZOOM app to your phone or tablet
Enter the meeting ID number you were given at your scheduled appointment time and the HEALTHY KIDS CLINIC Provider will appear on your screen!

shared_text:
Youthfest
March 16 at 7:48 PM ·

Due to the recent COVID-19 pandemic, school closings, the CDC’s recommendation of no gatherings larger than 50 people, and the President’s request of gatherings no larger than 10 people, Youthfest 2020 has been postponed.

However, for the last 17 years Youthfest has been a staple in our community during the month of March. Therefore, on Friday March 27, Saturday March 28, and Sunday March 29 tune into Facebook Live to worship with us. We are confident that even as our service looks different at this time, the Word of God will go forward and not return void.

***Stay tuned for an announcement with our postponed Youthfest date***
